Minutes.

State files an Amended Information charging the defendant with the following charges:
Count 1 - Injury by Negligent use of Dangerous Weapon, contrary to Section 940.24(1) of the Wisconsin Statutes;
Count 2 - Disorderly conduct, contrary to Section 947.01(1) of the Wisconsin Statutes;
Count 3 - Disorderly conduct, contrary to Section 947.01(1) of the Wisconsin Statutes.  
Guilty pleas entered to all three counts.  Convicted on Count 2 and 3.   
As to Count 1 - Court withholds entry of judgment of conviction, reviews the Deferred Judgment Agreement, approves it and signs it.  Review  05-01-2017.  
Count 2 & 3 - Sentences are withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for two (2) years.  Conditions of probation are:
1) Maintain full-time employment or participate in a work search per PO directive;
2) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
3) No assaultive contact with Dawn Spencer;
4) No weapons, including knives and BB guns, unless he is hunting with his grandfather, John Meunier, or doing target practice in the company of his grandfather;
5) Contact with Payton Spencer only as approved by the PO;
6) Any counseling deemed appropriate by the PO;
7) Forty-five (45) days jail, Ten (10) days, to be served up front, under the Huber Law, commencing on 12-02-14 by 6:00 p.m.  Thirty-five (35) days stayed, to be imposed upon the agents discretion.  
8) Pay costs of action;
9) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
